column5: \rVice Principal Mrs. Keating and I are proud to be Batey Bobcats! The educational foundation in place at Edna Batey speaks\rto the hard work and dedication of the staff and community in the previous years and we are excited to be a part of this\rschool.\rThe EGUSD mission is to challenge all of our students to realize their greatest potential. That is clearly evident in all that our\rstaff supports for our students. We are committed to a region-wide effort that supports our district's mission
column6: from our\rTransitional K classes through 12th grade. The administrators of the Pleasant Grove Region recognize that it takes all of us\rto work together.\rWe welcome parents as partners in their child's learning adventure. Parent involvement is an essential component of our\rschool. Your support is given
column8: and appreciated. Some parents help plan the programs and policies
column11: or serve as art docents. We welcome parental input at any time through\rour School Site Council meetings
column14: or any number of other committees.\rParents also support student success by providing space
column16: and encouragement for daily homework and by sending a\rclear message that education and regular school attendance are important to the family.\rAt Batey
column17: our Positive Behavioral Interventions and Support (PBIS) system continues to be successful. Together we support\rthe BOBCAT PACT and expect students and staff to honor our agreements to Be Safe
column20: and\rResourceful. We enjoy a positive school environment not only for our students
column21: but for our staff and parents as well. Thank\ryou for your continued support.\rRespectfully

column6: or necessary projects. Emergency repair needs are immediately resolved by either the\rschool custodian or district maintenance staff. Our Learning Center team works with teachers to support\rstudents who are on an Individualized Education Program (IEP) or are not meeting grade level standards. Strong\rcollaboration between the general education staff and the Learning Center ensure that all students have an opportunity to be\rsuccessful in school. We support an Inclusion program and ASD classes for students who qualify for the programs. Our\rintervention team includes teachers that support English Learners in the classroom in small groups. We offer some\rIntersession and Extended Day classes based on student need. Our GATE program has been revitalized and currently being\rdeveloped to meet the needs of 4-6 graders who are ready for the challenge of an accelerated program. We will seek out\rstudents who are eligible for GATE testing and support them in the classroom as needed. We pride ourselves on meeting the\rneeds of all.  ...                Unnamed: 3
